column5: just took these with my cell phone camera it had 9 scorable points and only one of which did not grow off the main beam!

That's a nice score for sure. I have a nice set of sheds myself i found years ago belonging to a beautiful 10 point. This year i found a single spike antler. 1 point about 7-8 inches long. They are always a treat to come across of any size.

this is the most cherished for some obvious reasons being a possible 18 point buck but the second favorite is off of what would have been an 8 pointer but the brow tine being 11" is what makes that shed a dandy

You know, I found one of those a couple of years back hiking in the Grey/Bruce area.  About 100 yards further into the bush, my cousin found the other......it was a little strange to say the least!

I found one many years ago at a friend's cottage. Took it home made a plaque and had the family name carved out of it and mounted the antler. It now sits inside his front door and used as a hat rack, better there tha in my garage.
I found a "3 pointer" half peice in Scarborough   Pretty neat find
Post the pic of that big brow tine!   Here's my 10 point set.
thats a nice set for sure would post the brow tine buck if i had a pic the rack is hanging at the camp!
